  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing quality primary education to 9,000 out-of-school children (8-11, 60% girls) in South Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Just 37% of girls in South Sudan go to school. 6% complete primary education. Schools are far away, with few women teachers and of poor quality. Girls often end up married or pregnant very early. They live at constant risk of conflict. The project is setting up 300 one-room community schools. The poorest and most at-risk children aged 8-11 (60% girls) will do three years of education and successfully move into the government system. Staff will train and support local women as teachers so they are more confident and earn their own livelihood. School Management Committees and parents&#x2019; forums will protect children better from harm.</narrative>
  </description>
